# ── User Profile — Facebook-style /:username ─────────────
# MUST be last. Netlify matches rules top-to-bottom, first match wins.
# Every named route above is already matched before this catch-all fires,
# so /home, /feed, /settings etc. are never accidentally swallowed here.
# user.js reads the path via usernameFromPath() and queries Supabase
# for the matching profile. Unknown usernames render a "User not found" state.
/:username  /app/user/index.html        200
